description: PbBi₂Se₄ is MAX Phase-like structured and crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one PbBi₂Se₄ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Pb(1)²⁺ is bonded to six equivalent Se(2)²⁻ atoms to form PbSe₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Bi(1)Se₆ octahedra, edges with six equivalent Pb(1)Se₆ octahedra, and edges with six equivalent Bi(1)Se₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 1°. All Pb(1)-Se(2) bond lengths are 3.068 Å. Bi(1)³⁺ is bonded to three equivalent Se(1)²⁻ and three equivalent Se(2)²⁻ atoms to form BiSe₆ octahedra that share corners with three equivalent Pb(1)Se₆ octahedra, edges with three equivalent Pb(1)Se₆ octahedra, and edges with six equivalent Bi(1)Se₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 1°. All Bi(1)-Se(1) bond lengths are 2.882 Å. All Bi(1)-Se(2) bond lengths are 3.117 Å. There are two inequivalent Se²⁻ sites. In the first Se²⁻ site, Se(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted T-shaped geometry to three equivalent Bi(1)³⁺ atoms. In the second Se²⁻ site, Se(2)²⁻ is bonded to three equivalent Pb(1)²⁺ and three equivalent Bi(1)³⁺ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing SeBi₃Pb₃ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted.

C is rhombohedral graphite-like structured and crystallizes in the hexagonal P6/mmm space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one C sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. C(1) is bonded in a trigonal planar geometry to three equivalent C(1) atoms. All C(1)-C(1) bond lengths are 1.423 Å.

NbS₂ is trigonal omega-like structured and crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one NbS₂ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Nb(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to six equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing NbS₆ octahedra. All Nb(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.497 Å. S(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted T-shaped geometry to three equivalent Nb(1)⁴⁺ atoms.

TiOBr crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pmmn space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one TiOBr sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Ti(1)³⁺ is bonded to four equivalent O(1)²⁻ and two equivalent Br(1)¹⁻ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing TiBr₂O₄ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 6°. There are two shorter (2.024 Å) and two longer (2.063 Å) Ti(1)-O(1) bond lengths. Both Ti(1)-Br(1) bond lengths are 2.587 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a see-saw-like geometry to four equivalent Ti(1)³⁺ atoms. Br(1)¹⁻ is bonded in an L-shaped geometry to two equivalent Ti(1)³⁺ atoms.

CaClF crystallizes in the tetragonal P4/nmm space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one CaClF sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Ca(1)²⁺ is bonded in a 8-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Cl(1)¹⁻ and four equivalent F(1)¹⁻ atoms. All Ca(1)-Cl(1) bond lengths are 2.919 Å. All Ca(1)-F(1) bond lengths are 2.326 Å. Cl(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Ca(1)²⁺ atoms. F(1)¹⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Ca(1)²⁺ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing FCa₄ tetrahedra.

HfNBr crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pmmn space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one HfNBr sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Hf(1)⁴⁺ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to four equivalent N(1)³⁻ and two equivalent Br(1)¹⁻ atoms. There are two shorter (2.131 Å) and two longer (2.135 Å) Hf(1)-N(1) bond lengths. Both Hf(1)-Br(1) bond lengths are 2.738 Å. N(1)³⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Hf(1)⁴⁺ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing NHf₄ tetrahedra. Br(1)¹⁻ is bonded in an L-shaped geometry to two equivalent Hf(1)⁴⁺ atoms.

SbN crystallizes in the triclinic P1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one SbN sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Sb(1,2)³⁺ is bonded in a distorted T-shaped geometry to three equivalent N(1,2)³⁻ atoms. There is one shorter (2.112 Å) and two longer (2.119 Å) Sb(1,2)-N(1,2) bond lengths. N(1,2)³⁻ is bonded in a distorted trigonal non-coplanar geometry to three equivalent Sb(1,2)³⁺ atoms.

ZnWO₄ crystallizes in the monoclinic P2 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one ZnWO₄ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. W(1)⁶⁺ is bonded to four equivalent O(1,2)²⁻ atoms to form WO₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent Zn(1)O₄ tetrahedra. All W(1)-O(1,2) bond lengths are 1.805 Å. Zn(1)²⁺ is bonded to four equivalent O(1,2)²⁻ atoms to form ZnO₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent W(1)O₄ tetrahedra. All Zn(1)-O(1,2) bond lengths are 1.984 Å. O(1,2)²⁻ is bonded in a bent 120 degrees geometry to one W(1)⁶⁺ and one Zn(1)²⁺ atom.

YbOBr crystallizes in the tetragonal P4/nmm space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one YbOBr sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Yb(1)³⁺ is bonded in a 8-coordinate geometry to four equivalent O(1)²⁻ and four equivalent Br(1)¹⁻ atoms. All Yb(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.266 Å. All Yb(1)-Br(1) bond lengths are 3.066 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Yb(1)³⁺ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing OYb₄ tetrahedra. Br(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Yb(1)³⁺ atoms.

SnS₂ is trigonal omega-like structured and crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one SnS₂ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Sn(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to six equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing SnS₆ octahedra. All Sn(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.600 Å. S(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted T-shaped geometry to three equivalent Sn(1)⁴⁺ atoms.

CoTeO₄ crystallizes in the monoclinic P2/m space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one CoTeO₄ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Co(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to two equivalent O(2)²⁻ and four equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form distorted CoO₆ octahedra that share edges with two equivalent Co(1)O₆ octahedra and edges with four equivalent Te(1)O₆ octahedra. Both Co(1)-O(2) bond lengths are 2.198 Å. All Co(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.046 Å. Te(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to two equivalent O(1)²⁻ and four equivalent O(2)²⁻ atoms to form TeO₆ octahedra that share edges with two equivalent Te(1)O₆ octahedra and edges with four equivalent Co(1)O₆ octahedra. Both Te(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.939 Å. All Te(1)-O(2) bond lengths are 2.047 Å. There are two inequivalent O²⁻ sites. In the first O²⁻ site, O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a trigonal non-coplanar geometry to two equivalent Co(1)⁴⁺ and one Te(1)⁴⁺ atom. In the second O²⁻ site, O(2)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted T-shaped geometry to one Co(1)⁴⁺ and two equivalent Te(1)⁴⁺ atoms.

CrSe crystallizes in the tetragonal P4/nmm space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one CrSe sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Cr(1)²⁺ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Se(1)²⁻ atoms. All Cr(1)-Se(1) bond lengths are 2.431 Å. Se(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Cr(1)²⁺ atoms.

AgInP₂S₆ crystallizes in the trigonal P312 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one AgInP₂S₆ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Ag(1)¹⁺ is bonded to six equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms to form AgS₆ octahedra that share edges with three equivalent In(1)S₆ octahedra. All Ag(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.785 Å. In(1)¹⁺ is bonded to six equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms to form InS₆ octahedra that share edges with three equivalent Ag(1)S₆ octahedra. All In(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.683 Å. P(1)⁵⁺ is bonded in a trigonal non-coplanar geometry to three equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms. All P(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.044 Å. S(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted trigonal non-coplanar geometry to one Ag(1)¹⁺, one In(1)¹⁺, and one P(1)⁵⁺ atom.

Ta₂PdS₆ crystallizes in the monoclinic C2/m space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one Ta₂PdS₆ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Ta(1)⁵⁺ is bonded to two equivalent S(2)²⁻, two equivalent S(3)²⁻, and three equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and face-sharing TaS₇ pentagonal bipyramids. Both Ta(1)-S(2) bond lengths are 2.504 Å. Both Ta(1)-S(3) bond lengths are 2.495 Å. There are two shorter (2.499 Å) and one longer (2.627 Å) Ta(1)-S(1) bond length. Pd(1)²⁺ is bonded in a square co-planar geometry to two equivalent S(2)²⁻ and two equivalent S(3)²⁻ atoms. Both Pd(1)-S(2) bond lengths are 2.356 Å. Both Pd(1)-S(3) bond lengths are 2.355 Å. There are three inequivalent S²⁻ sites. In the first S²⁻ site, S(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted trigonal non-coplanar geometry to three equivalent Ta(1)⁵⁺ atoms. In the second S²⁻ site, S(2)²⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Ta(1)⁵⁺ and one Pd(1)²⁺ atom. In the third S²⁻ site, S(3)²⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Ta(1)⁵⁺ and one Pd(1)²⁺ atom.

TiSe is lead oxide-like structured and crystallizes in the tetragonal P4/nmm space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one TiSe sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Ti(1)²⁺ is bonded to four equivalent Se(1)²⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing TiSe₄ tetrahedra. All Ti(1)-Se(1) bond lengths are 2.532 Å. Se(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Ti(1)²⁺ atoms.

ZrFeCl₆ is Chromium trichloride-derived structured and crystallizes in the trigonal P312 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one ZrFeCl₆ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Zr(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to six equivalent Cl(1)¹⁻ atoms to form ZrCl₆ octahedra that share edges with three equivalent Fe(1)Cl₆ octahedra. All Zr(1)-Cl(1) bond lengths are 2.488 Å. Fe(1)²⁺ is bonded to six equivalent Cl(1)¹⁻ atoms to form FeCl₆ octahedra that share edges with three equivalent Zr(1)Cl₆ octahedra. All Fe(1)-Cl(1) bond lengths are 2.469 Å. Cl(1)¹⁻ is bonded in an L-shaped geometry to one Zr(1)⁴⁺ and one Fe(1)²⁺ atom.

RbI₃ crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pmc2₁ space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one RbI₃ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Rb(1) is bonded to one I(1), two equivalent I(2), and two equivalent I(3) atoms to form distorted corner-sharing RbI₅ trigonal bipyramids. The Rb(1)-I(1) bond length is 4.132 Å. There is one shorter (3.564 Å) and one longer (3.661 Å) Rb(1)-I(2) bond length. There is one shorter (3.586 Å) and one longer (3.591 Å) Rb(1)-I(3) bond length. There are three inequivalent I sites. In the first I site, I(1) is bonded in a distorted trigonal planar geometry to one Rb(1), one I(2), and one I(3) atom. The I(1)-I(2) bond length is 2.956 Å. The I(1)-I(3) bond length is 3.001 Å. In the second I site, I(2) is bonded in a distorted linear geometry to two equivalent Rb(1) and one I(1) atom. In the third I site, I(3) is bonded in a distorted bent 150 degrees geometry to two equivalent Rb(1) and one I(1) atom.

SmSI is Cotunnite-derived structured and crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one SmSI sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Sm(1)³⁺ is bonded in a 7-coordinate geometry to four equivalent S(1)²⁻ and three equivalent I(1)¹⁻ atoms. There are three shorter (2.743 Å) and one longer (2.837 Å) Sm(1)-S(1) bond length. All Sm(1)-I(1) bond lengths are 3.309 Å. S(1)²⁻ is bonded to four equivalent Sm(1)³⁺ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing SSm₄ tetrahedra. I(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Sm(1)³⁺ atoms.

PbBi₂Te₄ is MAX Phase-like structured and crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one PbBi₂Te₄ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Pb(1)²⁺ is bonded to six equivalent Te(2)²⁻ atoms to form PbTe₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Bi(1)Te₆ octahedra, edges with six equivalent Pb(1)Te₆ octahedra, and edges with six equivalent Bi(1)Te₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 1°. All Pb(1)-Te(2) bond lengths are 3.248 Å. Bi(1)³⁺ is bonded to three equivalent Te(1)²⁻ and three equivalent Te(2)²⁻ atoms to form BiTe₆ octahedra that share corners with three equivalent Pb(1)Te₆ octahedra, edges with three equivalent Pb(1)Te₆ octahedra, and edges with six equivalent Bi(1)Te₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 1°. All Bi(1)-Te(1) bond lengths are 3.088 Å. All Bi(1)-Te(2) bond lengths are 3.297 Å. There are two inequivalent Te²⁻ sites. In the first Te²⁻ site, Te(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted T-shaped geometry to three equivalent Bi(1)³⁺ atoms. In the second Te²⁻ site, Te(2)²⁻ is bonded to three equivalent Pb(1)²⁺ and three equivalent Bi(1)³⁺ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing TeBi₃Pb₃ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted.

InOBr crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pmmn space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one InOBr sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. In(1)³⁺ is bonded to four equivalent O(1)²⁻ and two equivalent Br(1)¹⁻ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing InBr₂O₄ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 37°. There are two shorter (2.158 Å) and two longer (2.274 Å) In(1)-O(1) bond lengths. Both In(1)-Br(1) bond lengths are 2.691 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded to four equivalent In(1)³⁺ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing OIn₄ tetrahedra. Br(1)¹⁻ is bonded in an L-shaped geometry to two equivalent In(1)³⁺ atoms.

OBr₂ is Indium-like structured and crystallizes in the monoclinic P2₁ space group. The structure is zero-dimensional and consists of two OBr₂ clusters. O(1) is bonded in a bent 120 degrees geometry to one Br(1) and one Br(2) atom. The O(1)-Br(1) bond length is 1.953 Å. The O(1)-Br(2) bond length is 1.849 Å. There are two inequivalent Br sites. In the first Br site, Br(1) is bonded in a single-bond geometry to one O(1) atom. In the second Br site, Br(2) is bonded in a distorted single-bond geometry to one O(1) atom.

NSCl crystallizes in the monoclinic Pm space group. The structure is one-dimensional and consists of one NSCl ribbon oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. There are two inequivalent N³⁺ sites. In the first N³⁺ site, N(1)³⁺ is bonded in a distorted bent 120 degrees geometry to one S(1)²⁻ and one S(2)²⁻ atom. The N(1)-S(1) bond length is 1.596 Å. The N(1)-S(2) bond length is 1.609 Å. In the second N³⁺ site, N(2)³⁺ is bonded in a bent 120 degrees geometry to two equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms. Both N(2)-S(1) bond lengths are 1.600 Å. There are two inequivalent S²⁻ sites. In the first S²⁻ site, S(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted single-bond geometry to one N(1)³⁺, one N(2)³⁺, and one Cl(1)¹⁻ atom. The S(1)-Cl(1) bond length is 2.216 Å. In the second S²⁻ site, S(2)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted trigonal non-coplanar geometry to two equivalent N(1)³⁺, one Cl(2)¹⁻, and two equivalent Cl(1)¹⁻ atoms. The S(2)-Cl(2) bond length is 2.162 Å. Both S(2)-Cl(1) bond lengths are 3.453 Å. There are two inequivalent Cl¹⁻ sites. In the first Cl¹⁻ site, Cl(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a 2-coordinate geometry to one S(1)²⁻ and one S(2)²⁻ atom. In the second Cl¹⁻ site, Cl(2)¹⁻ is bonded in a single-bond geometry to one S(2)²⁻ atom.

Ta₂S₂C crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one Ta₂S₂C sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Ta(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to three equivalent C(1)⁴⁻ and three equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing TaC₃S₃ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted. All Ta(1)-C(1) bond lengths are 2.241 Å. All Ta(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.499 Å. C(1)⁴⁻ is bonded to six equivalent Ta(1)⁴⁺ atoms to form edge-sharing CTa₆ octahedra. S(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Ta(1)⁴⁺ atoms.

UNTe crystallizes in the tetragonal P4/nmm space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one UNTe sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. U(1)⁵⁺ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to four equivalent N(1)³⁻ and four equivalent Te(1)²⁻ atoms. All U(1)-N(1) bond lengths are 2.255 Å. All U(1)-Te(1) bond lengths are 3.227 Å. N(1)³⁻ is bonded to four equivalent U(1)⁵⁺ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing NU₄ tetrahedra. Te(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to four equivalent U(1)⁵⁺ atoms.

Te(HO₂)₂ crystallizes in the monoclinic Pc space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one Te(HO₂)₂ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. There are two inequivalent H¹⁺ sites. In the first H¹⁺ site, H(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a single-bond geometry to one O(1)²⁻ atom. The H(1)-O(1) bond length is 0.996 Å. In the second H¹⁺ site, H(2)¹⁺ is bonded in a single-bond geometry to one O(2)²⁻ atom. The H(2)-O(2) bond length is 0.995 Å. Te(1)⁶⁺ is bonded to one O(1)²⁻, one O(2)²⁻, two equivalent O(3)²⁻, and two equivalent O(4)²⁻ atoms to form corner-sharing TeO₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles range from 45-46°. The Te(1)-O(1) bond length is 1.950 Å. The Te(1)-O(2) bond length is 1.950 Å. There is one shorter (1.942 Å) and one longer (1.957 Å) Te(1)-O(3) bond length. There is one shorter (1.940 Å) and one longer (1.959 Å) Te(1)-O(4) bond length. There are four inequivalent O²⁻ sites. In the first O²⁻ site, O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a water-like geometry to one H(1)¹⁺ and one Te(1)⁶⁺ atom. In the second O²⁻ site, O(2)²⁻ is bonded in a water-like geometry to one H(2)¹⁺ and one Te(1)⁶⁺ atom. In the third O²⁻ site, O(3)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted bent 150 degrees geometry to two equivalent Te(1)⁶⁺ atoms. In the fourth O²⁻ site, O(4)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted bent 120 degrees geometry to two equivalent Te(1)⁶⁺ atoms.

FeS is lead oxide-like structured and crystallizes in the tetragonal P4/nmm space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one FeS sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Fe(1)²⁺ is bonded to four equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing FeS₄ tetrahedra. All Fe(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.171 Å. S(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Fe(1)²⁺ atoms.

Lix₀CoO₂ is trigonal omega-like structured and crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one Lix₀CoO₂ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Co(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing CoO₆ octahedra. All Co(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.876 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Co(1)⁴⁺ atoms.

Np(OF)₂ crystallizes in the hexagonal P6/mmm space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one Np(OF)₂ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Np(1)⁶⁺ is bonded to two equivalent O(1)²⁻ and six equivalent F(1)¹⁻ atoms to form distorted edge-sharing NpO₂F₆ hexagonal bipyramids. Both Np(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.775 Å. All Np(1)-F(1) bond lengths are 2.422 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a single-bond geometry to one Np(1)⁶⁺ atom. F(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a trigonal planar geometry to three equivalent Np(1)⁶⁺ atoms.

Si₃H crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one Si₃H sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. There are three inequivalent Si sites. In the first Si site, Si(1) is bonded in a single-bond geometry to three equivalent Si(2) and one H(1) atom. All Si(1)-Si(2) bond lengths are 2.366 Å. The Si(1)-H(1) bond length is 1.510 Å. In the second Si site, Si(2) is bonded to one Si(3) and three equivalent Si(1) atoms to form corner-sharing SiSi₄ tetrahedra. The Si(2)-Si(3) bond length is 2.391 Å. In the third Si site, Si(3) is bonded to one Si(2) and three equivalent Si(3) atoms to form corner-sharing SiSi₄ tetrahedra. All Si(3)-Si(3) bond lengths are 2.378 Å. H(1) is bonded in a single-bond geometry to one Si(1) atom.

TiTe₂ is trigonal omega-like structured and crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one TiTe₂ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Ti(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to six equivalent Te(1)²⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing TiTe₆ octahedra. All Ti(1)-Te(1) bond lengths are 2.780 Å. Te(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted T-shaped geometry to three equivalent Ti(1)⁴⁺ atoms.

Ta₃SBr₇ crystallizes in the monoclinic Cm space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one Ta₃SBr₇ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Ta(1,2)³⁺ is bonded to one S(1)²⁻; one Br(2)¹⁻; two equivalent Br(1,5)¹⁻; and two equivalent Br(3,4)¹⁻ atoms to form distorted edge-sharing TaSBr₅ octahedra. The Ta(1,2)-S(1) bond length is 2.415 Å. The Ta(1,2)-Br(2) bond length is 2.826 Å. Both Ta(1,2)-Br(1,5) bond lengths are 2.692 Å. Both Ta(1,2)-Br(3,4) bond lengths are 2.571 Å. S(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Ta(1,2)³⁺ atoms. There are three inequivalent Br¹⁻ sites. In the first Br¹⁻ site, Br(1,5)¹⁻ is bonded in a water-like geometry to two equivalent Ta(1,2)³⁺ atoms. In the second Br¹⁻ site, Br(2)¹⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Ta(1,2)³⁺ atoms. In the third Br¹⁻ site, Br(3,4)¹⁻ is bonded in a 2-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Ta(1,2)³⁺ atoms.

TiSe₂ is trigonal omega-like structured and crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one TiSe₂ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Ti(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to six equivalent Se(1)²⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing TiSe₆ octahedra. All Ti(1)-Se(1) bond lengths are 2.560 Å. Se(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted T-shaped geometry to three equivalent Ti(1)⁴⁺ atoms.

Co(ClO₄)₂ crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one Co(ClO₄)₂ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Co(1) is bonded to six equivalent O(1) atoms to form CoO₆ octahedra that share corners with six equivalent Cl(1)O₄ tetrahedra. All Co(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.073 Å. There are two inequivalent O sites. In the first O site, O(1) is bonded in a bent 120 degrees geometry to one Co(1) and one Cl(1) atom. The O(1)-Cl(1) bond length is 1.479 Å. In the second O site, O(2) is bonded in a single-bond geometry to one Cl(1) atom. The O(2)-Cl(1) bond length is 1.413 Å. Cl(1) is bonded to one O(2) and three equivalent O(1) atoms to form ClO₄ tetrahedra that share corners with three equivalent Co(1)O₆ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedral tilt angles are 47°.

CrS₂ is trigonal omega-like structured and crystallizes in the monoclinic C2/m space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one CrS₂ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Cr(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to six equivalent S(1)²⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing CrS₆ octahedra. All Cr(1)-S(1) bond lengths are 2.349 Å. S(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted T-shaped geometry to three equivalent Cr(1)⁴⁺ atoms.

Lix₀CoO₂ is Cyanogen Chloride-derived structured and crystallizes in the hexagonal P6/mmm space group. The structure is zero-dimensional and consists of one Lix₀CoO₂ cluster. Co(1)⁴⁺ is bonded in a linear geometry to two equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms. Both Co(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.586 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a single-bond geometry to one Co(1)⁴⁺ atom.

VBr₂ is trigonal omega-like structured and crystallizes in the trigonal P̅3m1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one VBr₂ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. V(1)²⁺ is bonded to six equivalent Br(1)¹⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing VBr₆ octahedra. All V(1)-Br(1) bond lengths are 2.638 Å. Br(1)¹⁻ is bonded in a distorted T-shaped geometry to three equivalent V(1)²⁺ atoms.

VOBr₂ crystallizes in the orthorhombic Pmmm space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one VOBr₂ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. V(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to two equivalent O(1)²⁻ and four equivalent Br(1)¹⁻ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing VBr₄O₂ octahedra. The corner-sharing octahedra are not tilted. Both V(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.810 Å. All V(1)-Br(1) bond lengths are 2.551 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a linear geometry to two equivalent V(1)⁴⁺ atoms. Br(1)¹⁻ is bonded in an L-shaped geometry to two equivalent V(1)⁴⁺ atoms.

AgBiO₂ crystallizes in the monoclinic P2₁/m space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one AgBiO₂ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Ag(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a distorted linear geometry to one O(1)²⁻ and one O(2)²⁻ atom. The Ag(1)-O(1) bond length is 2.061 Å. The Ag(1)-O(2) bond length is 2.084 Å. Bi(1)³⁺ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to two equivalent O(1)²⁻ and three equivalent O(2)²⁻ atoms. Both Bi(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 2.245 Å. There is one shorter (2.173 Å) and two longer (2.467 Å) Bi(1)-O(2) bond lengths. There are two inequivalent O²⁻ sites. In the first O²⁻ site, O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted single-bond geometry to one Ag(1)¹⁺ and two equivalent Bi(1)³⁺ atoms. In the second O²⁻ site, O(2)²⁻ is bonded to one Ag(1)¹⁺ and three equivalent Bi(1)³⁺ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and corner-sharing OAgBi₃ tetrahedra.

KAgSe is Parent of FeAs superconductors-derived structured and crystallizes in the tetragonal P4/nmm space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one KAgSe sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. K(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 8-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Ag(1)¹⁺ and four equivalent Se(1)²⁻ atoms. All K(1)-Ag(1) bond lengths are 3.467 Å. All K(1)-Se(1) bond lengths are 3.257 Å. Ag(1)¹⁺ is bonded to four equivalent K(1)¹⁺ and four equivalent Se(1)²⁻ atoms to form a mixture of distorted edge and face-sharing AgK₄Se₄ tetrahedra. All Ag(1)-Se(1) bond lengths are 2.819 Å. Se(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 8-coordinate geometry to four equivalent K(1)¹⁺ and four equivalent Ag(1)¹⁺ atoms.

HgPSe₃ crystallizes in the triclinic P̅1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one HgPSe₃ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Hg(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 6-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Se(1)²⁻, two equivalent Se(2)²⁻, and two equivalent Se(3)²⁻ atoms. There is one shorter (2.674 Å) and one longer (3.012 Å) Hg(1)-Se(1) bond length. There is one shorter (2.615 Å) and one longer (3.479 Å) Hg(1)-Se(2) bond length. There is one shorter (2.847 Å) and one longer (3.506 Å) Hg(1)-Se(3) bond length. P(1)⁵⁺ is bonded in a trigonal non-coplanar geometry to one Se(1)²⁻, one Se(2)²⁻, and one Se(3)²⁻ atom. The P(1)-Se(1) bond length is 2.243 Å. The P(1)-Se(2) bond length is 2.233 Å. The P(1)-Se(3) bond length is 2.172 Å. There are three inequivalent Se²⁻ sites. In the first Se²⁻ site, Se(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted trigonal non-coplanar geometry to two equivalent Hg(1)¹⁺ and one P(1)⁵⁺ atom. In the second Se²⁻ site, Se(2)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted water-like geometry to two equivalent Hg(1)¹⁺ and one P(1)⁵⁺ atom. In the third Se²⁻ site, Se(3)²⁻ is bonded in a 2-coordinate geometry to two equivalent Hg(1)¹⁺ and one P(1)⁵⁺ atom.

Lix₀CoO₂ is trigonal omega-like structured and crystallizes in the triclinic P̅1 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one Lix₀CoO₂ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Co(1)⁴⁺ is bonded to six equivalent O(1)²⁻ atoms to form edge-sharing CoO₆ octahedra. All Co(1)-O(1) bond lengths are 1.876 Å. O(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 3-coordinate geometry to three equivalent Co(1)⁴⁺ atoms.

CuInP₂Se₆ crystallizes in the trigonal P312 space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one CuInP₂Se₆ sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Cu(1)¹⁺ is bonded to six equivalent Se(1)²⁻ atoms to form CuSe₆ octahedra that share edges with three equivalent In(1)Se₆ octahedra. All Cu(1)-Se(1) bond lengths are 2.694 Å. In(1)¹⁺ is bonded to six equivalent Se(1)²⁻ atoms to form InSe₆ octahedra that share edges with three equivalent Cu(1)Se₆ octahedra. All In(1)-Se(1) bond lengths are 2.808 Å. P(1)⁵⁺ is bonded in a trigonal non-coplanar geometry to three equivalent Se(1)²⁻ atoms. All P(1)-Se(1) bond lengths are 2.222 Å. Se(1)²⁻ is bonded in a distorted trigonal non-coplanar geometry to one Cu(1)¹⁺, one In(1)¹⁺, and one P(1)⁵⁺ atom.

Sb crystallizes in the hexagonal P6/mmm space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one Sb sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Sb(1) is bonded in a hexagonal planar geometry to six equivalent Sb(1) atoms. All Sb(1)-Sb(1) bond lengths are 3.152 Å.

RbMnP crystallizes in the tetragonal P4/nmm space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one RbMnP sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Rb(1)¹⁺ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to four equivalent P(1)³⁻ atoms. All Rb(1)-P(1) bond lengths are 3.353 Å. Mn(1)²⁺ is bonded to four equivalent P(1)³⁻ atoms to form a mixture of edge and corner-sharing MnP₄ tetrahedra. All Mn(1)-P(1) bond lengths are 2.292 Å. P(1)³⁻ is bonded in a 8-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Rb(1)¹⁺ and four equivalent Mn(1)²⁺ atoms.

RbLiSe crystallizes in the tetragonal P4/nmm space group. The structure is two-dimensional and consists of one RbLiSe sheet oriented in the (0, 0, 1) direction. Rb(1)¹⁺ is bonded to four equivalent Se(1)²⁻ atoms to form distorted RbSe₄ trigonal pyramids that share corners with eight equivalent Li(1)Se₄ tetrahedra, corners with four equivalent Rb(1)Se₄ trigonal pyramids, edges with four equivalent Li(1)Se₄ tetrahedra, and edges with four equivalent Rb(1)Se₄ trigonal pyramids. All Rb(1)-Se(1) bond lengths are 3.407 Å. Li(1)¹⁺ is bonded to four equivalent Se(1)²⁻ atoms to form LiSe₄ tetrahedra that share corners with four equivalent Li(1)Se₄ tetrahedra, corners with eight equivalent Rb(1)Se₄ trigonal pyramids, edges with four equivalent Li(1)Se₄ tetrahedra, and edges with four equivalent Rb(1)Se₄ trigonal pyramids. All Li(1)-Se(1) bond lengths are 2.635 Å. Se(1)²⁻ is bonded in a 4-coordinate geometry to four equivalent Rb(1)¹⁺ and four equivalent Li(1)¹⁺ atoms.
